    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="964"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d964">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5611/9–1154</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-11">September 11,
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">Cabot</persName>
                    </hi>: In the absence of the Secretary, I am writing to acknowledge your letter
                    to him of August 26, 1954, enclosing a letter from <persName
                        corresp="#p_SEARSM1">Mason Sears</persName> and endorsing his views on the
                    importance of carrying out promises made to the Marshall Islanders in connection
                    with our nuclear experiments in the Marshall Islands. I heartily concur with the
                    views expressed by you and Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SEARSM1">Sears</persName>
                    and am sending copies of your letter and that of Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_SEARSM1">Sears</persName> to the Atomic Energy Commission and
                    the Departments of the Interior and Defense. Copies of my letter of transmittal
                    are enclosed. I have asked that this matter be pursued energetically so that we
                    may present the best possible record when our activities in the Trust Territory
                    of the Pacific Islands are discussed in United Nations bodies.</p>
                <p>To assist you in dealing with this question when it arises, I am requesting that
                    you and Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SEARSM1">Sears</persName> be kept informed of
                    the steps taken to keep the promises to which you have referred. I am also
                    enclosing a brief note of acknowledgement to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SEARSM1"
                        >Sears</persName> which I would appreciate your passing on to him when he
                    returns from Africa.<note n="1" xml:id="d964fn1">Letter to <persName
                            corresp="#p_SEARSM1">Sears</persName> not printed. It was virtually
                        identical with the text of the letter to <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1"
                            >Lodge</persName>, except for the following statement: “I am sure the
                        Secretary would wish me to express his appreciation to you for stressing the
                        importance of this matter.…” (799.021/9–1154)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Faithfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SMITHWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Walter B. Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
